When managing the links, you may want to test a redirect. For this to work, this app must know what link you will use in front of the keys, as they are often different from your main domain (usually shorter).
The short domain which we'll probably use
used for testing the links - typically http://

The key length - you usually want to limit this either to 3 or another short value, to make it type-able
Will auto-prepend this into all generated links. You can add one or more, comma-separated.
The domain the links will point to if they were relative. Leave blank to stay in this domain, but often it's a longer domain as the short-links typically use a cryptic domain.

This is how much error-correction is built into the image. We recommend to use the lowest value, as more error correction actually makes the QR harder to scan.
